{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884293681,"sessionID":"ses_2850c860affeZNdDKKGycv8yCT","part":{"id":"prt_d7af3cb12001g0rhAwQRYVUmHP","messageID":"msg_d7af3c2a40015J8ttPjrshjaSu","sessionID":"ses_2850c860affeZNdDKKGycv8yCT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_cdb17e9b3917464989dea214","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 本提案实现 AgentCube 项目的 GitHub Actions CI/CD 流水线体系，为代码质量、构建验证、镜像发布、安全扫描提供自动化流水线。该 CI/CD 体系是 AgentCube 工程化实践的核心基础设施，支撑持续集成、持续交付、质量门禁全流程。\n6: \n7: 目标是：\n8: \n9: 1. **代码质量门禁** - 在 PR 和 push 事件中自动运行 lint、typecheck、test，确保代码质量\n10: 2. **构建验证** - 验证 Go 和 Python 代码可编译，Docker 镜像可构建\n11: 3. **多架构支持** - 构建 amd64、arm64 多架构 Docker 镜像，支持异构集群\n12: 4. **镜像发布** - 自动推送镜像到 GHCR，支持版本标签管理（latest, commit-sha, semver）\n13: 5. **安全扫描** - 集成 Trivy 扫描镜像漏洞，集成 CodeQL 扫描代码安全问题\n14: 6. **文档站点** - 自动构建和部署 Docusaurus 文档到 GitHub Pages\n15: 7. **发布自动化** - 创建 GitHub Release，生成变更日志，上传构建产物\n16: 8. **依赖更新** - 自动检测依赖更新，创建 Dependabot PR\n17: \n18: 本提案基于 AR-032（Dockerfile 多阶段构建）、AR-033（Makefile 构建目标）实现，遵循 GitHub Actions 最佳实践和 AgentCube 工程规范。\n19: \n20: ## Scope\n21: \n22: **Module:** .github  \n23: **Language:** YAML  \n24: **Size:** L\n25: \n26: 本 AR 包含：\n27: \n28: - **包含内容：**\n29:   - `.github/workflows/ci.yml` - CI 流水线（lint, test, build）\n30:   - `.github/workflows/cd.yml` - CD 流水线（镜像推送、发布）\n31:   - `.github/workflows/security-scan.yml` - 安全扫描（Trivy, CodeQL）\n32:   - `.github/workflows/docs.yml` - 文档构建和部署\n33:   - `.github/workflows/multi-arch-build.yml` - 多架构镜像构建\n34:   - `.github/workflows/e2e-test.yml` - 端到端测试\n35:   - `.github/workflows/nightly-build.yml` - 夜间构建\n36:   - `.github/workflows/pr-validation.yml` - PR 验证\n37:   - `.github/workflows/release.yml` - Release 发布\n38:   - `.github/workflows/dependency-review.yml` - 依赖审查\n39:   - `.github/workflows/stale.yml` -  stale 管理\n40:   - `.github/workflows/labeler.yml` - 自动标签\n41:   - `.github/dependabot.yml` - Dependabot 配置\n42:   - `.github/labeler.yml` - 自动标签规则\n43:   - `.github/CODEOWNERS` - 代码所有者\n44:   - 相关 Action 配置和脚本\n45: \n46: - **不包含内容：**\n47:   - Dockerfile 编写（由 AR-032 管理）\n48:   - Makefile 编写（由 AR-033 管理）\n49:   - Helm Chart 打包发布（由 AR-030 管理）\n50:   - 文档内容编写（由文档团队管理）\n51: \n52: ## Current State Analysis\n53: \n54: ### 现有 CI/CD 状态\n55: \n56: 根据项目结构检查：\n57: - 无 `.github/workflows/` 目录\n58: - 无 `.github/dependabot.yml`\n59: - 无 `.github/CODEOWNERS`\n60: - 无现有 GitHub Actions 配置\n61: \n62: ### 参考设计规范\n63: \n64: 根据 `project.md` 和 AR-032、AR-033：\n65: \n66: **技术栈要求：**\n67: - Go 1.24 - 需要配置 Go 环境\n68: - Python ≥3.10 - 需要配置 Python 环境\n69: - Docker - 需要 Docker in Docker 或 Runner 预装\n70: - Helm 3 - 需要 Helm 工具\n71: - Kubernetes - 需要 Kind 或 K3s 进行测试\n72: \n73: **镜像仓库：**\n74: - GHCR (ghcr.io/volcano-sh) - GitHub Container Registry\n75: - 标签策略：latest, <commit-sha>, <version>\n76: \n77: **发布流程：**\n78: - Git tag 触发 Release\n79: - 语义化版本：vMajor.Minor.Patch\n80: - 自动生成交付物\n81: \n82: ### 差距分析\n83: \n84: 1. **缺少工作流文件** - 无任何 GitHub Actions 工作流\n85: 2. **缺少依赖管理** - 无 Dependabot 配置\n86: 3. **缺少代码所有者** - 无 CODEOWNERS 配置\n87: 4. **缺少标签管理** - 无自动标签规则\n88: 5. **缺少安全策略** - 无安全扫描配置\n89: \n90: ### 项目特殊需求\n91: \n92: 根据 AgentCube 架构：\n93: \n94: 1. **Kubernetes 测试** - 需要 Kind 集群测试 K8s 集成\n95: 2. **Redis 测试** - 需要 Redis 服务测试缓存层\n96: 3. **多组件构建** - Workload Manager、Router、Volcano Agent Scheduler 三个组件\n97: 4. **Python SDK/CLI** - 需要 Python 包构建和发布\n98: 5. **Helm Chart** - 需要 Helm lint 和打包\n99: 6. **文档站点** - Docusaurus 构建和部署\n100: \n101: ## Proposed Changes\n102: \n103: ### 1. 目录结构\n104: \n105: ```\n106: .github/\n107: ├── workflows/\n108: │   ├── ci.yml                      # CI 主流水线\n109: │   ├── cd.yml                      # CD 发布流水线\n110: │   ├── security-scan.yml           # 安全扫描\n111: │   ├── docs.yml                    # 文档部署\n112: │   ├── multi-arch-build.yml        # 多架构构建\n113: │   ├── e2e-test.yml                # 端到端测试\n114: │   ├── nightly-build.yml           # 夜间构建\n115: │   ├── pr-validation.yml           # PR 验证\n116: │   ├── release.yml                 # Release 发布\n117: │   ├── dependency-review.yml       # 依赖审查\n118: │   ├── stale.yml                   # Stale 管理\n119: │   └── labeler.yml                 # 自动标签\n120: ├── dependabot.yml                  # Dependabot 配置\n121: ├── labeler.yml                     # 标签规则\n122: └── CODEOWNERS                      # 代码所有者\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ### 2. CI 主流水线 (ci.yml)\n126: \n127: ```yaml\n128: # .github/workflows/ci.yml\n129: name: CI\n130: \n131: on:\n132:   push:\n133:     branches: [main, develop]\n134:   pull_request:\n135:     branches: [main, develop]\n136: \n137: env:\n138:   GO_VERSION: '1.24'\n139:   PYTHON_VERSION: '3.11'\n140:   NODE_VERSION: '20'\n141: \n142: permissions:\n143:   contents: read\n144: \n145: jobs:\n146:   go-lint:\n147:     name: Go Lint\n148:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n149:     steps:\n150:       - name: Checkout\n151:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n152: \n153:       - name: Setup Go\n154:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n155:         with:\n156:           go-version: ${{ env.GO_VERSION }}\n157:           cache: true\n158: \n159:       - name: Run golangci-lint\n160:         uses: golangci/golangci-lint-action@v6\n161:         with:\n162:           version: latest\n163:           args: --timeout=5m\n164: \n165:   go-test:\n166:     name: Go Test\n167:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n168:     services:\n169:       redis:\n170:         image: redis:7-alpine\n171:         ports:\n172:           - 6379:6379\n173:     steps:\n174:       - name: Checkout\n175:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n176: \n177:       - name: Setup Go\n178:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n179:         with:\n180:           go-version: ${{ env.GO_VERSION }}\n181:           cache: true\n182: \n183:       - name: Run tests\n184:         run: go test -race -coverprofile=coverage.out ./...\n185: \n186:       - name: Upload coverage\n187:         uses: codecov/codecov-action@v4\n188:         with:\n189:           file: ./coverage.out\n190:           flags: go\n191: \n192:   python-lint:\n193:     name: Python Lint\n194:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n195:     steps:\n196:       - name: Checkout\n197:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n198: \n199:       - name: Setup Python\n200:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n201:         with:\n202:           python-version: ${{ env.PYTHON_VERSION }}\n203: \n204:       - name: Install dependencies\n205:         run: |\n206:           pip install ruff mypy\n207:           pip install -e sdk-python/\n208: \n209:       - name: Run ruff\n210:         run: ruff check sdk-python/ cmd/cli/\n211: \n212:       - name: Run mypy\n213:         run: mypy sdk-python/ cmd/cli/\n214: \n215:   python-test:\n216:     name: Python Test\n217:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n218:     services:\n219:       redis:\n220:         image: redis:7-alpine\n221:         ports:\n222:           - 6379:6379\n223:     steps:\n224:       - name: Checkout\n225:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n226: \n227:       - name: Setup Python\n228:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n229:         with:\n230:           python-version: ${{ env.PYTHON_VERSION }}\n231: \n232:       - name: Install dependencies\n233:         run: |\n234:           pip install pytest pytest-cov\n235:           pip install -e sdk-python/\n236: \n237:       - name: Run tests\n238:         run: pytest --cov=sdk-python sdk-python/ tests/\n239: \n240:       - name: Upload coverage\n241:         uses: codecov/codecov-action@v4\n242:         with:\n243:           file: ./coverage.xml\n244:           flags: python\n245: \n246:   helm-lint:\n247:     name: Helm Lint\n248:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n249:     steps:\n250:       - name: Checkout\n251:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n252: \n253:       - name: Setup Helm\n254:         uses: azure/setup-helm@v3\n255:         with:\n256:           version: v3.14.0\n257: \n258:       - name: Run helm lint\n259:         run: helm lint manifests/\n260: \n261:   build-verify:\n262:     name: Build Verify\n263:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n264:     needs: [go-lint, go-test, python-lint, python-test]\n265:     steps:\n266:       - name: Checkout\n267:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n268: \n269:       - name: Setup Go\n270:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n271:         with:\n272:           go-version: ${{ env.GO_VERSION }}\n273: \n274:       - name: Build Go binaries\n275:         run: |\n276:           go build -o /tmp/workloadmanager ./cmd/agentcube\n277:           go build -o /tmp/router ./cmd/agentcube-proxy\n278:           go build -o /tmp/volcano-agent-scheduler ./cmd/agentd\n279: \n280:       - name: Setup Python\n281:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n282:         with:\n283:           python-version: ${{ env.PYTHON_VERSION }}\n284: \n285:       - name: Build Python packages\n286:         run: |\n287:           pip install build\n288:           python -m build sdk-python/\n289: ```\n290: \n291: ### 3. CD 发布流水线 (cd.yml)\n292: \n293: ```yaml\n294: # .github/workflows/cd.yml\n295: name: CD\n296: \n297: on:\n298:   push:\n299:     branches: [main]\n300:     tags:\n301:       - 'v*'\n302: \n303: env:\n304:   REGISTRY: ghcr.io\n305:   IMAGE_NAMESPACE: volcano-sh\n306: \n307: permissions:\n308:   contents: read\n309:   packages: write\n310:   id-token: write\n311: \n312: jobs:\n313:   build-and-push-images:\n314:     name: Build and Push Images\n315:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n316:     if: github.event_name == 'push' && startsWith(github.ref, 'refs/tags/v')\n317:     steps:\n318:       - name: Checkout\n319:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n320: \n321:       - name: Setup Docker Buildx\n322:         uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3\n323: \n324:       - name: Login to GHCR\n325:         uses: docker/login-action@v3\n326:         with:\n327:           registry: ${{ env.REGISTRY }}\n328:           username: ${{ github.actor }}\n329:           password: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n330: \n331:       - name: Extract metadata\n332:         id: meta\n333:         uses: docker/metadata-action@v5\n334:         with:\n335:           images: |\n336:             ${{ env.REGISTRY }}/${{ env.IMAGE_NAMESPACE }}/workloadmanager\n337:             ${{ env.REGISTRY }}/${{ env.IMAGE_NAMESPACE }}/router\n338:             ${{ env.REGISTRY }}/${{ env.IMAGE_NAMESPACE }}/volcano-agent-scheduler\n339:           tags: |\n340:             type=semver,pattern={{version}}\n341:             type=semver,pattern={{major}}.{{minor}}\n342:             type=sha,prefix=\n343: \n344:       - name: Build and push Workload Manager\n345:         uses: docker/build-push-action@v5\n346:         with:\n347:           context: .\n348:           file: deployment/docker/Dockerfile.workloadmanager\n349:           push: true\n350:           tags: ${{ steps.meta.outputs.tags }}\n351:           platforms: linux/amd64,linux/arm64\n352:           cache-from: type=gha\n353:           cache-to: type=gha,mode=max\n354: \n355:       - name: Build and push Router\n356:         uses: docker/build-push-action@v5\n357:         with:\n358:           context: .\n359:           file: deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router\n360:           push: true\n361:           tags: ${{ steps.meta.outputs.tags }}\n362:           platforms: linux/amd64,linux/arm64\n363:           cache-from: type=gha\n364:           cache-to: type=gha,mode=max\n365: \n366:       - name: Build and push Volcano Agent Scheduler\n367:         uses: docker/build-push-action@v5\n368:         with:\n369:           context: .\n370:           file: deployment/docker/Dockerfile.volcano-agent-scheduler\n371:           push: true\n372:           tags: ${{ steps.meta.outputs.tags }}\n373:           platforms: linux/amd64,linux/arm64\n374:           cache-from: type=gha\n375:           cache-to: type=gha,mode=max\n376: \n377:   publish-helm-chart:\n378:     name: Publish Helm Chart\n379:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n380:     needs: build-and-push-images\n381:     if: github.event_name == 'push' && startsWith(github.ref, 'refs/tags/v')\n382:     steps:\n383:       - name: Checkout\n384:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n385:         with:\n386:           fetch-depth: 0\n387: \n388:       - name: Setup Helm\n389:         uses: azure/setup-helm@v3\n390:         with:\n391:           version: v3.14.0\n392: \n393:       - name: Configure Git\n394:         run: |\n395:           git config user.name \"$GITHUB_ACTOR\"\n396:           git config user.email \"$GITHUB_ACTOR@users.noreply.github.com\"\n397: \n398:       - name: Run chart-releaser\n399:         uses: helm/chart-releaser-action@v1.6.0\n400:         with:\n401:           charts_dir: manifests/\n402:         env:\n403:           CR_TOKEN: \"${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\"\n404: ```\n405: \n406: ### 4. 安全扫描 (security-scan.yml)\n407: \n408: ```yaml\n409: # .github/workflows/security-scan.yml\n410: name: Security Scan\n411: \n412: on:\n413:   push:\n414:     branches: [main, develop]\n415:   pull_request:\n416:     branches: [main]\n417:   schedule:\n418:     - cron: '0 2 * * 1' # Weekly on Monday\n419: \n420: permissions:\n421:   contents: read\n422:   security-events: write\n423:   actions: read\n424: \n425: jobs:\n426:   trivy-scan:\n427:     name: Trivy Container Scan\n428:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n429:     steps:\n430:       - name: Checkout\n431:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n432: \n433:       - name: Build images for scanning\n434:         run: |\n435:           docker build -f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.workloadmanager -t localhost/workloadmanager:scan .\n436:           docker build -f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router -t localhost/router:scan .\n437:           docker build -f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.volcano-agent-scheduler -t localhost/volcano-agent-scheduler:scan .\n438: \n439:       - name: Run Trivy scanner\n440:         uses: aquasecurity/trivy-action@master\n441:         with:\n442:           image-ref: localhost/workloadmanager:scan\n443:           format: 'sarif'\n444:           output: 'trivy-workloadmanager.sarif'\n445:           severity: 'CRITICAL,HIGH'\n446: \n447:       - name: Upload Trivy results\n448:         uses: github/codeql-action/upload-sarif@v3\n449:         with:\n450:           sarif_file: 'trivy-workloadmanager.sarif'\n451: \n452:   codeql-scan:\n453:     name: CodeQL Code Scan\n454:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n455:     steps:\n456:       - name: Checkout\n457:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n458: \n459:       - name: Setup Go\n460:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n461:         with:\n462:           go-version: '1.24'\n463: \n464:       - name: Initialize CodeQL\n465:         uses: github/codeql-action/init@v3\n466:         with:\n467:           languages: go, python\n468:           queries: security-extended\n469: \n470:       - name: Autobuild\n471:         uses: github/codeql-action/autobuild@v3\n472: \n473:       - name: Perform CodeQL Analysis\n474:         uses: github/codeql-action/analyze@v3\n475:         with:\n476:           category: \"/language:go,python\"\n477: \n478:   go-security:\n479:     name: Go Security Scan\n480:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n481:     steps:\n482:       - name: Checkout\n483:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n484: \n485:       - name: Setup Go\n486:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n487:         with:\n488:           go-version: '1.24'\n489: \n490:       - name: Run gosec\n491:         uses: securego/gosec@master\n492:         with:\n493:           args: ./...\n494: \n495:   dependency-audit:\n496:     name: Python Dependency Audit\n497:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n498:     steps:\n499:       - name: Checkout\n500:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n501: \n502:       - name: Setup Python\n503:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n504:         with:\n505:           python-version: '3.11'\n506: \n507:       - name: Install audit tools\n508:         run: pip install safety pip-audit\n509: \n510:       - name: Run safety check\n511:         run: safety check -r sdk-python/requirements.txt\n512: \n513:       - name: Run pip-audit\n514:         run: pip-audit -r sdk-python/requirements.txt\n515: ```\n516: \n517: ### 5. 文档部署 (docs.yml)\n518: \n519: ```yaml\n520: # .github/workflows/docs.yml\n521: name: Docs\n522: \n523: on:\n524:   push:\n525:     branches: [main]\n526:     paths:\n527:       - 'docs/**'\n528:       - 'website/**'\n529: \n530: permissions:\n531:   contents: read\n532:   pages: write\n533:   id-token: write\n534: \n535: jobs:\n536:   build-and-deploy:\n537:     name: Build and Deploy Docs\n538:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n539:     environment:\n540:       name: github-pages\n541:       url: ${{ steps.deployment.outputs.page_url }}\n542:     steps:\n543:       - name: Checkout\n544:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n545: \n546:       - name: Setup Node.js\n547:         uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n548:         with:\n549:           node-version: '20'\n550:           cache: 'npm'\n551:           cache-dependency-path: website/package-lock.json\n552: \n553:       - name: Install dependencies\n554:         run: cd website && npm ci\n555: \n556:       - name: Build site\n557:         run: cd website && npm run build\n558: \n559:       - name: Setup Pages\n560:         uses: actions/configure-pages@v4\n561: \n562:       - name: Upload artifact\n563:         uses: actions/upload-pages-artifact@v3\n564:         with:\n565:           path: './website/build'\n566: \n567:       - name: Deploy to GitHub Pages\n568:         id: deployment\n569:         uses: actions/deploy-pages@v4\n570: ```\n571: \n572: ### 6. 多架构构建 (multi-arch-build.yml)\n573: \n574: ```yaml\n575: # .github/workflows/multi-arch-build.yml\n576: name: Multi-Arch Build\n577: \n578: on:\n579:   push:\n580:     branches: [main]\n581:     paths:\n582:       - 'cmd/**'\n583:       - 'pkg/**'\n584:       - 'deployment/docker/**'\n585:   pull_request:\n586:     paths:\n587:       - 'cmd/**'\n588:       - 'pkg/**'\n589:       - 'deployment/docker/**'\n590: \n591: permissions:\n592:   contents: read\n593: \n594: jobs:\n595:   build-multi-arch:\n596:     name: Build Multi-Arch Images\n597:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n598:     strategy:\n599:       matrix:\n600:         component: [workloadmanager, router, volcano-agent-scheduler]\n601:         platform: [linux/amd64, linux/arm64]\n602:     steps:\n603:       - name: Checkout\n604:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n605: \n606:       - name: Setup Docker Buildx\n607:         uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3\n608: \n609:       - name: Build ${{ matrix.component }} for ${{ matrix.platform }}\n610:         run: |\n611:           docker buildx build \\\n612:             --platform ${{ matrix.platform }} \\\n613:             -t ghcr.io/volcano-sh/${{ matrix.component }}:${{ github.sha }} \\\n614:             --load \\\n615:             -f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.${{ matrix.component }} \\\n616:             .\n617: \n618:       - name: Test image\n619:         run: |\n620:           docker run --rm ghcr.io/volcano-sh/${{ matrix.component }}:${{ github.sha }} --help\n621: ```\n622: \n623: ### 7. 端到端测试 (e2e-test.yml)\n624: \n625: ```yaml\n626: # .github/workflows/e2e-test.yml\n627: name: E2E Test\n628: \n629: on:\n630:   pull_request:\n631:     branches: [main]\n632:     paths:\n633:       - 'cmd/**'\n634:       - 'pkg/**'\n635:       - 'manifests/**'\n636:       - 'testing/**'\n637: \n638: permissions:\n639:   contents: read\n640: \n641: jobs:\n642:   e2e-test:\n643:     name: E2E Test\n644:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n645:     timeout-minutes: 30\n646:     steps:\n647:       - name: Checkout\n648:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n649: \n650:       - name: Setup Go\n651:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n652:         with:\n653:           go-version: '1.24'\n654: \n655:       - name: Setup Python\n656:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n657:         with:\n658:           python-version: '3.11'\n659: \n660:       - name: Setup Kind\n661:         uses: helm/kind-action@v1.9.0\n662:         with:\n663:           version: v0.20.0\n664:           node_image: kindest/node:v1.28.0\n665: \n666:       - name: Install Redis\n667:         run: |\n668:           kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bitnami/charts/main/bitnami/redis/templates/deployment.yaml\n669:           kubectl wait --for=condition=available deployment/redis --timeout=120s\n670: \n671:       - name: Install AgentCube\n672:         run: |\n673:           helm install agentcube manifests/ \\\n674:             --set image.repository=localhost:5000 \\\n675:             --set redis.host=redis.default.svc.cluster.local\n676: \n677:       - name: Wait for deployment\n678:         run: |\n679:           kubectl wait --for=condition=available deployment/workloadmanager --timeout=300s\n680:           kubectl wait --for=condition=available deployment/router --timeout=300s\n681: \n682:       - name: Run E2E tests\n683:         run: |\n684:           pip install pytest\n685:           pytest testing/e2e/ -v\n686: \n687:       - name: Collect logs on failure\n688:         if: failure()\n689:         run: |\n690:           kubectl get pods -A\n691:           kubectl logs -l app=workloadmanager\n692:           kubectl logs -l app=router\n693: ```\n694: \n695: ### 8. 夜间构建 (nightly-build.yml)\n696: \n697: ```yaml\n698: # .github/workflows/nightly-build.yml\n699: name: Nightly Build\n700: \n701: on:\n702:   schedule:\n703:     - cron: '0 2 * * *' # Daily at 2 AM UTC\n704:   workflow_dispatch:\n705: \n706: permissions:\n707:   contents: read\n708:   packages: write\n709: \n710: jobs:\n711:   nightly-build:\n712:     name: Nightly Build\n713:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n714:     steps:\n715:       - name: Checkout\n716:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n717: \n718:       - name: Setup Docker Buildx\n719:         uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3\n720: \n721:       - name: Login to GHCR\n722:         uses: docker/login-action@v3\n723:         with:\n724:           registry: ghcr.io\n725:           username: ${{ github.actor }}\n726:           password: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n727: \n728:       - name: Build and push nightly images\n729:         run: |\n730:           make docker-build-all\n731:           make docker-push-all\n732:         env:\n733:           DOCKER_TAG: nightly-${{ github.run_id }}\n734: ```\n735: \n736: ### 9. PR 验证 (pr-validation.yml)\n737: \n738: ```yaml\n739: # .github/workflows/pr-validation.yml\n740: name: PR Validation\n741: \n742: on:\n743:   pull_request_target:\n744:     types: [opened, edited, synchronize, reopened, labeled]\n745: \n746: permissions:\n747:   pull-requests: write\n748:   contents: read\n749: \n750: jobs:\n751:   validate-pr-title:\n752:     name: Validate PR Title\n753:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n754:     steps:\n755:       - name: Check PR title\n756:         uses: amannn/action-semantic-pull-request@v5\n757:         env:\n758:           GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n759:         with:\n760:           types: |\n761:             feat\n762:             fix\n763:             docs\n764:             style\n765:             refactor\n766:             perf\n767:             test\n768:             build\n769:             ci\n770:             chore\n771:             revert\n772:           requireScope: false\n773: \n774:   validate-pr-body:\n775:     name: Validate PR Body\n776:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n777:     steps:\n778:       - name: Check PR has description\n779:         uses: actions/github-script@v7\n780:         with:\n781:           script: |\n782:             const pr = context.payload.pull_request;\n783:             if (!pr.body || pr.body.trim() === '') {\n784:               core.setFailed('PR description is required');\n785:             }\n786: \n787:   check-issues-linked:\n788:     name: Check Issues Linked\n789:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n790:     steps:\n791:       - name: Check for linked issues\n792:         uses: actions/github-script@v7\n793:         with:\n794:           script: |\n795:             const pr = context.payload.pull_request;\n796:             const body = pr.body || '';\n797:             if (!body.match(/(close|closes|closed|fix|fixes|fixed|resolve|resolves|resolved)\\s#(\\d+)/i)) {\n798:               console.log('No linked issues found (optional)');\n799:             }\n800: ```\n801: \n802: ### 10. Release 发布 (release.yml)\n803: \n804: ```yaml\n805: # .github/workflows/release.yml\n806: name: Release\n807: \n808: on:\n809:   push:\n810:     tags:\n811:       - 'v*'\n812: \n813: permissions:\n814:   contents: write\n815:   packages: write\n816:   id-token: write\n817: \n818: jobs:\n819:   create-release:\n820:     name: Create Release\n821:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n822:     outputs:\n823:       upload_url: ${{ steps.create_release.outputs.upload_url }}\n824:       version: ${{ steps.get_version.outputs.version }}\n825:     steps:\n826:       - name: Checkout\n827:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n828:         with:\n829:           fetch-depth: 0\n830: \n831:       - name: Get version\n832:         id: get_version\n833:         run: echo \"version=${GITHUB_REF#refs/tags/}\" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT\n834: \n835:       - name: Generate changelog\n836:         uses: mikepenz/release-changelog-builder-action@v4\n837:         id: changelog\n838:         with:\n839:           configuration: .github/release-config.json\n840: \n841:       - name: Create Release\n842:         id: create_release\n843:         uses: softprops/action-gh-release@v1\n844:         with:\n845:           body: ${{ steps.changelog.outputs.changelog }}\n846:           draft: false\n847:           prerelease: false\n848:         env:\n849:           GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n850: \n851:   publish-python-sdk:\n852:     name: Publish Python SDK\n853:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n854:     needs: create-release\n855:     steps:\n856:       - name: Checkout\n857:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n858: \n859:       - name: Setup Python\n860:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n861:         with:\n862:           python-version: '3.11'\n863: \n864:       - name: Install build tools\n865:         run: pip install build twine\n866: \n867:       - name: Build package\n868:         run: python -m build sdk-python/\n869: \n870:       - name: Publish to PyPI\n871:         uses: pypa/gh-action-pypi-publish@release/v1\n872:         with:\n873:           packages-dir: sdk-python/dist/\n874:           password: ${{ secrets.PYPI_API_TOKEN }}\n875: \n876:   publish-cli-tool:\n877:     name: Publish CLI Tool\n878:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n879:     needs: create-release\n880:     steps:\n881:       - name: Checkout\n882:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n883: \n884:       - name: Setup Python\n885:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n886:         with:\n887:           python-version: '3.11'\n888: \n889:       - name: Install build tools\n890:         run: pip install build twine\n891: \n892:       - name: Build CLI\n893:         run: python -m build cmd/cli/\n894: \n895:       - name: Publish to PyPI\n896:         uses: pypa/gh-action-pypi-publish@release/v1\n897:         with:\n898:           packages-dir: cmd/cli/dist/\n899:           password: ${{ secrets.PYPI_API_TOKEN }}\n900: \n901:   sign-artifacts:\n902:     name: Sign Artifacts\n903:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n904:     needs: create-release\n905:     steps:\n906:       - name: Checkout\n907:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n908: \n909:       - name: Setup cosign\n910:         uses: sigstore/cosign-installer@v3\n911: \n912:       - name: Sign images\n913:         run: |\n914:           cosign sign ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:${{ needs.create-release.outputs.version }}\n915:           cosign sign ghcr.io/volcano-sh/router:${{ needs.create-release.outputs.version }}\n916:           cosign sign ghcr.io/volcano-sh/volcano-agent-scheduler:${{ needs.create-release.outputs.version }}\n917:         env:\n918:           COSIGN_EXPERIMENTAL: \"true\"\n919: ```\n920: \n921: ### 11. 依赖审查 (dependency-review.yml)\n922: \n923: ```yaml\n924: # .github/workflows/dependency-review.yml\n925: name: Dependency Review\n926: \n927: on:\n928:   pull_request:\n929:     branches: [main, develop]\n930: \n931: permissions:\n932:   contents: read\n933: \n934: jobs:\n935:   dependency-review:\n936:     name: Dependency Review\n937:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n938:     steps:\n939:       - name: Checkout\n940:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n941: \n942:       - name: Dependency Review\n943:         uses: actions/dependency-review-action@v4\n944:         with:\n945:           fail-on-severity: high\n946:           deny-licenses: GPL-3.0, AGPL-3.0\n947: \n948:   go-dependency-check:\n949:     name: Go Dependency Check\n950:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n951:     steps:\n952:       - name: Checkout\n953:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n954: \n955:       - name: Setup Go\n956:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n957:         with:\n958:           go-version: '1.24'\n959: \n960:       - name: Run govulncheck\n961:         run: |\n962:           go install golang.org/x/vuln/cmd/govulncheck@latest\n963:           govulncheck ./...\n964: \n965:   python-dependency-check:\n966:     name: Python Dependency Check\n967:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n968:     steps:\n969:       - name: Checkout\n970:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n971: \n972:       - name: Setup Python\n973:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n974:         with:\n975:           python-version: '3.11'\n976: \n977:       - name: Run pip-audit\n978:         run: |\n979:           pip install pip-audit\n980:           pip-audit -r sdk-python/requirements.txt\n981:           pip-audit -r cmd/cli/requirements.txt\n982: ```\n983: \n984: ### 12. Stale 管理 (stale.yml)\n985: \n986: ```yaml\n987: # .github/workflows/stale.yml\n988: name: Stale\n989: \n990: on:\n991:   schedule:\n992:     - cron: '0 0 * * *' # Daily\n993:   workflow_dispatch:\n994: \n995: permissions:\n996:   issues: write\n997:   pull-requests: write\n998: \n999: jobs:\n1000:   stale:\n1001:     name: Close Stale Issues and PRs\n1002:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n1003:     steps:\n1004:       - name: Close stale issues and PRs\n1005:         uses: actions/stale@v9\n1006:         with:\n1007:           stale-issue-message: 'This issue has been automatically marked as stale because it has not had recent activity. It will be closed if no further activity occurs.'\n1008:           stale-pr-message: 'This PR has been automatically marked as stale because it has not had recent activity. It will be closed if no further activity occurs.'\n1009:           close-issue-message: 'This issue was closed because it has been stalled for 30 days with no activity.'\n1010:           close-pr-message: 'This PR was closed because it has been stalled for 30 days with no activity.'\n1011:           days-before-issue-stale: 60\n1012:           days-before-pr-stale: 30\n1013:           days-before-issue-close: 90\n1014:           days-before-pr-close: 60\n1015:           exempt-issue-labels: 'bug,enhancement,help wanted,good first issue'\n1016:           exempt-pr-labels: 'bug,enhancement,help wanted'\n1017:           stale-issue-label: 'stale'\n1018:           stale-pr-label: 'stale'\n1019:           remove-stale-when-updated: true\n1020:           operations-per-run: 100\n1021: ```\n1022: \n1023: ### 13. 自动标签 (labeler.yml)\n1024: \n1025: ```yaml\n1026: # .github/workflows/labeler.yml\n1027: name: Labeler\n1028: \n1029: on:\n1030:   - pull_request_target\n1031: \n1032: permissions:\n1033:   contents: read\n1034:   pull-requests: write\n1035: \n1036: jobs:\n1037:   label:\n1038:     name: Apply Labels\n1039:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n1040:     steps:\n1041:       - name: Apply Labels\n1042:         uses: actions/labeler@v5\n1043:         with:\n1044:           repo-token: \"${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\"\n1045:           configuration-path: .github/labeler.yml\n1046: ```\n1047: \n1048: ### 14. Dependabot 配置 (dependabot.yml)\n1049: \n1050: ```yaml\n1051: # .github/dependabot.yml\n1052: version: 2\n1053: updates:\n1054:   # Go dependencies\n1055:   - package-ecosystem: \"gomod\"\n1056:     directory: \"/\"\n1057:     schedule:\n1058:       interval: \"weekly\"\n1059:       day: \"monday\"\n1060:       time: \"02:00\"\n1061:     open-pull-requests-limit: 10\n1062:     labels:\n1063:       - \"dependencies\"\n1064:       - \"go\"\n1065:     commit-message:\n1066:       prefix: \"chore(go)\"\n1067:       include: \"scope\"\n1068:     groups:\n1069:       k8s-io:\n1070:         patterns:\n1071:           - \"k8s.io/*\"\n1072:           - \"sigs.k8s.io/*\"\n1073:       volcano:\n1074:         patterns:\n1075:           - \"volcano.sh/*\"\n1076: \n1077:   # Python dependencies\n1078:   - package-ecosystem: \"pip\"\n1079:     directory: \"/sdk-python\"\n1080:     schedule:\n1081:       interval: \"weekly\"\n1082:       day: \"monday\"\n1083:       time: \"02:00\"\n1084:     open-pull-requests-limit: 10\n1085:     labels:\n1086:       - \"dependencies\"\n1087:       - \"python\"\n1088:     commit-message:\n1089:       prefix: \"chore(python)\"\n1090:       include: \"scope\"\n1091: \n1092:   - package-ecosystem: \"pip\"\n1093:     directory: \"/cmd/cli\"\n1094:     schedule:\n1095:       interval: \"weekly\"\n1096:       day: \"monday\"\n1097:       time: \"02:00\"\n1098:     open-pull-requests-limit: 10\n1099:     labels:\n1100:       - \"dependencies\"\n1101:       - \"python\"\n1102:     commit-message:\n1103:       prefix: \"chore(cli)\"\n1104:       include: \"scope\"\n1105: \n1106:   # GitHub Actions\n1107:   - package-ecosystem: \"github-actions\"\n1108:     directory: \"/\"\n1109:     schedule:\n1110:       interval: \"weekly\"\n1111:       day: \"monday\"\n1112:       time: \"02:00\"\n1113:     open-pull-requests-limit: 10\n1114:     labels:\n1115:       - \"dependencies\"\n1116:       - \"github-actions\"\n1117:     commit-message:\n1118:       prefix: \"chore(actions)\"\n1119:       include: \"scope\"\n1120: \n1121:   # Docker\n1122:   - package-ecosystem: \"docker\"\n1123:     directory: \"/deployment/docker\"\n1124:     schedule:\n1125:       interval: \"weekly\"\n1126:       day: \"monday\"\n1127:       time: \"02:00\"\n1128:     open-pull-requests-limit: 5\n1129:     labels:\n1130:       - \"dependencies\"\n1131:       - \"docker\"\n1132:     commit-message:\n1133:       prefix: \"chore(docker)\"\n1134:       include: \"scope\"\n1135: ```\n1136: \n1137: ### 15. 标签规则 (labeler.yml)\n1138: \n1139: ```yaml\n1140: # .github/labeler.yml\n1141: # Automatically apply labels to PRs based on file patterns\n1142: \n1143: go:\n1144:   - changed-files:\n1145:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1146:           - cmd/**/*.go\n1147:           - pkg/**/*.go\n1148:           - \"*.go\"\n1149:           - go.mod\n1150:           - go.sum\n1151: \n1152: python:\n1153:   - changed-files:\n1154:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1155:           - sdk-python/**/*.py\n1156:           - cmd/cli/**/*.py\n1157:           - \"**/requirements.txt\"\n1158: \n1159: documentation:\n1160:   - changed-files:\n1161:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1162:           - docs/**/*\n1163:           - website/**/*\n1164:           - \"*.md\"\n1165:           - README.md\n1166: \n1167: helm:\n1168:   - changed-files:\n1169:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1170:           - manifests/**/*.yaml\n1171:           - manifests/**/*.tpl\n1172:           - manifests/Chart.yaml\n1173:           - manifests/values.yaml\n1174: \n1175: docker:\n1176:   - changed-files:\n1177:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1178:           - deployment/docker/**/*\n1179:           - \"**/Dockerfile*\"\n1180:           - .dockerignore\n1181: \n1182: ci-cd:\n1183:   - changed-files:\n1184:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1185:           - .github/workflows/**/*\n1186:           - .github/dependabot.yml\n1187:           - .github/labeler.yml\n1188: \n1189: tests:\n1190:   - changed-files:\n1191:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1192:           - testing/**/*\n1193:           - \"**/*_test.go\"\n1194:           - \"**/test_*.py\"\n1195: \n1196: configuration:\n1197:   - changed-files:\n1198:       - any-glob-to-any-file:\n1199:           - \"*.yaml\"\n1200:           - \"*.yml\"\n1201:           - \"*.toml\"\n1202:           - Makefile\n1203:           - .golangci.yml\n1204: ```\n1205: \n1206: ### 16. 代码所有者 (CODEOWNERS)\n1207: \n1208: ```\n1209: # .github/CODEOWNERS\n1210: # Code owners for automatic review assignment\n1211: \n1212: # Default owners\n1213: * @agentcube-maintainers\n1214: \n1215: # Go code\n1216: /cmd/ @agentcube-go-team\n1217: /pkg/ @agentcube-go-team\n1218: \n1219: # Python SDK and CLI\n1220: /sdk-python/ @agentcube-python-team\n1221: /cmd/cli/ @agentcube-python-team\n1222: \n1223: # Kubernetes manifests\n1224: /manifests/ @agentcube-k8s-team\n1225: \n1226: # Documentation\n1227: /docs/ @agentcube-docs-team\n1228: /website/ @agentcube-docs-team\n1229: \n1230: # CI/CD\n1231: .github/ @agentcube-devops-team\n1232: \n1233: # Docker\n1234: /deployment/docker/ @agentcube-devops-team\n1235: \n1236: # Tests\n1237: /testing/ @agentcube-qa-team\n1238: ```\n1239: \n1240: ## Impact Analysis\n1241: \n1242: ### 依赖影响\n1243: \n1244: | 依赖项 | 版本 | 用途 |\n1245: |--------|------|------|\n1246: | GitHub Actions | - | CI/CD 平台 |\n1247: | Go | 1.24 | 应用编译 |\n1248: | Python | 3.11 | SDK/CLI 构建 |\n1249: | Node.js | 20 | 文档构建 |\n1250: | Docker | 预装 | 镜像构建 |\n1251: | Helm | 3.14+ | Chart 打包 |\n1252: | Kind | 0.20+ | E2E 测试集群 |\n1253: | Trivy | latest | 安全扫描 |\n1254: | CodeQL | v3 | 代码分析 |\n1255: \n1256: ### 模块依赖关系\n1257: \n1258: ```\n1259: .github/\n1260: ├── workflows/\n1261: │   ├── ci.yml                      # 依赖：Go, Python, Helm, Redis\n1262: │   ├── cd.yml                      # 依赖：AR-032 (Dockerfile), AR-033 (Makefile)\n1263: │   ├── security-scan.yml           # 依赖：Trivy, CodeQL, gosec\n1264: │   ├── docs.yml                    # 依赖：Node.js, Docusaurus\n1265: │   ├── multi-arch-build.yml        # 依赖：Docker Buildx\n1266: │   ├── e2e-test.yml                # 依赖：Kind, Helm, Redis\n1267: │   ├── nightly-build.yml           # 依赖：AR-033 (Makefile)\n1268: │   ├── pr-validation.yml           # 依赖：GitHub API\n1269: │   ├── release.yml                 # 依赖：PyPI, GHCR, cosign\n1270: │   ├── dependency-review.yml       # 依赖：govulncheck, pip-audit\n1271: │   ├── stale.yml                   # 依赖：GitHub API\n1272: │   └── labeler.yml                 # 依赖：labeler action\n1273: ├── dependabot.yml                  # 依赖：GitHub API\n1274: ├── labeler.yml                     # 依赖：labeler action\n1275: └── CODEOWNERS                      # 依赖：GitHub teams\n1276: ```\n1277: \n1278: ### 向后兼容性\n1279: \n1280: - 首次实现，无破坏性变更\n1281: - 工作流设计为增量式采纳，团队可选择性启用\n1282: - 依赖自动更新（Dependabot）确保 Action 版本更新\n1283: \n1284: ### 成本影响\n1285: \n1286: | 资源 | 月度估算 | 备注 |\n1287: |------|----------|------|\n1288: | GitHub Actions Minutes | 3000 分钟 | 免费额度 2000 分钟/月，超出需付费 |\n1289: | Storage (Packages) | 5 GB | GHCR 存储，免费 50GB |\n1290: | Actions Runners | Self-hosted (可选) | 减少成本，提高速度 |\n1291: \n1292: ### 安全影响\n1293: \n1294: - **Positive**: 自动化安全扫描，及时检测漏洞\n1295: - **Positive**: 依赖审查，阻止不安全依赖\n1296: - **Positive**: CodeQL 分析，发现代码安全问题\n1297: - **Consideration**: GHCR Token 权限管理，需最小权限原则\n1298: - **Consideration**: PyPI Token 存储，需使用 GitHub Secrets\n1299: \n1300: ## Alternatives Considered\n1301: \n1302: ### 方案 1: 使用 CircleCI 替代 GitHub Actions\n1303: \n1304: **优点:**\n1305: - 更灵活的配置选项\n1306: - 更好的并行执行能力\n1307: - 更便宜的定价\n1308: \n1309: **缺点:**\n1310: - 需要额外注册和配置\n1311: - 与 GitHub 集成度低\n1312: - 学习成本增加\n1313: \n1314: **决策:** 使用 GitHub Actions，保持与 GitHub 深度集成。\n1315: \n1316: ### 方案 2: 使用 Jenkins 自建 CI/CD\n1317: \n1318: **优点:**\n1319: - 完全控制\n1320: - 无使用限制\n1321: - 丰富的插件生态\n1322: \n1323: **缺点:**\n1324: - 维护成本高\n1325: - 需要基础设施\n1326: - 配置复杂\n1327: \n1328: **决策:** 使用 GitHub Actions，减少运维负担。\n1329: \n1330: ### 方案 3: 单个工作流文件（monolithic workflow）\n1331: \n1332: **优点:**\n1333: - 配置集中\n1334: - 易于理解整体流程\n1335: \n1336: **缺点:**\n1337: - 文件过大难以维护\n1338: - 无法独立触发/调试\n1339: - 执行效率低\n1340: \n1341: **决策:** 采用模块化设计，每个工作流独立职责。\n1342: \n1343: ### 方案 4: 使用 GitLab CI/CD\n1344: \n1345: **优点:**\n1346: - 原生集成 GitLab\n1347: - 强大的 YAML 语法\n1348: - 免费额度较高\n1349: \n1350: **缺点:**\n1351: - 需要迁移代码仓库\n1352: - 团队学习成本\n1353: - 生态锁定\n1354: \n1355: **决策:** 保持 GitHub，使用 GitHub Actions。\n1356: \n1357: ### 方案 5: 手动发布流程\n1358: \n1359: **优点:**\n1360: - 完全控制发布过程\n1361: - 无需配置工作流\n1362: \n1363: **缺点:**\n1364: - 容易出错\n1365: - 无法追溯\n1366: - 效率低下\n1367: \n1368: **决策:** 自动化发布，提高可靠性和效率。\n1369: \n1370: ## Testing Strategy\n1371: \n1372: ### 工作流验证\n1373: \n1374: 1. **语法验证** - 使用 `actionlint` 验证 YAML 语法\n1375: 2. **本地测试** - 使用 `act` 工具在本地运行工作流\n1376: 3. **Dry Run** - 在 PR 中测试工作流触发\n1377: \n1378: ### 集成测试\n1379: \n1380: 1. **CI 流水线测试** - 验证 lint, test, build 全部通过\n1381: 2. **CD 流水线测试** - 在 staging 环境验证发布\n1382: 3. **E2E 测试** - 验证 Kind 集群中完整部署\n1383: \n1384: ### 安全测试\n1385: \n1386: 1. **权限验证** - 验证 GITHUB_TOKEN 权限最小化\n1387: 2. **Secret 测试** - 验证 Secrets 未被泄露\n1388: 3. **依赖扫描** - 验证 Trivy/CodeQL 能检测问题\n1389: \n1390: ### 性能测试\n1391: \n1392: 1. **并行执行测试** - 验证并发作业不冲突\n1393: 2. **缓存测试** - 验证 Docker/Go 缓存命中率\n1394: 3. **超时测试** - 验证长运行作业有超时保护\n1395: \n1396: ### 测试覆盖目标\n1397: \n1398: - 工作流语法：100% 有效\n1399: - CI 触发：100%（push, PR）\n1400: - CD 触发：100%（tag）\n1401: - 安全扫描：100%（定期 + PR）\n1402: - 文档部署：100%（main 分支）\n1403: \n1404: ## Acceptance Criteria\n1405: \n1406: - [ ] `ci.yml` 在 PR 和 push 事件中成功触发\n1407: - [ ] `cd.yml` 在 tag 推送时成功发布镜像\n1408: - [ ] `security-scan.yml` 成功运行 Trivy 和 CodeQL\n1409: - [ ] `docs.yml` 成功部署文档到 GitHub Pages\n1410: - [ ] `multi-arch-build.yml` 成功构建 amd64 和 arm64 镜像\n1411: - [ ] `e2e-test.yml` 在 Kind 集群中成功运行 E2E 测试\n1412: - [ ] `nightly-build.yml` 按计划触发夜间构建\n1413: - [ ] `pr-validation.yml` 验证 PR 标题和描述\n1414: - [ ] `release.yml` 成功创建 GitHub Release 并发布 PyPI 包\n1415: - [ ] `dependency-review.yml` 成功检测依赖漏洞\n1416: - [ ] `stale.yml` 成功标记和关闭 stale 问题/PR\n1417: - [ ] `labeler.yml` 成功自动应用标签\n1418: - [ ] `dependabot.yml` 成功创建依赖更新 PR\n1419: - [ ] `labeler.yml` 文件规则正确匹配\n1420: - [ ] `CODEOWNERS` 正确分配审查者\n1421: - [ ] 所有工作流通过语法验证（actionlint）\n1422: - [ ] 所有 Secrets 配置正确\n1423: - [ ] 文档完整（使用说明、故障排查）\n1424: \n1425: ## Dependencies\n1426: \n1427: ### 必需依赖\n1428: - GitHub 仓库\n1429: - GitHub Actions 启用\n1430: - GHCR 访问权限\n1431: - PyPI 账号（发布 SDK/CLI）\n1432: \n1433: ### 可选依赖\n1434: - Codecov 账号（测试覆盖率）\n1435: - Self-hosted Runner（可选，降低成本）\n1436: - Slack/Discord Webhook（通知）\n1437: \n1438: ### 被依赖\n1439: - AR-032 (Dockerfile 多阶段构建) - 提供 Dockerfile\n1440: - AR-033 (Makefile 构建目标) - 提供 make 命令\n1441: - AR-030 (Helm Chart) - 提供 manifests/\n1442: \n1443: ## Migration Notes\n1444: \n1445: ### 从零到 CI/CD\n1446: \n1447: 1. **初始设置**\n1448:    - 创建 `.github/workflows/` 目录\n1449:    - 复制所有工作流文件\n1450:    - 配置 Dependabot 和 CODEOWNERS\n1451: \n1452: 2. **配置 Secrets**\n1453:    ```bash\n1454:    # 必需配置\n1455:    GITHUB_TOKEN (自动提供)\n1456:    PYPI_API_TOKEN (PyPI 发布)\n1457:    ```\n1458: \n1459: 3. **启用工作流**\n1460:    - 检查 GitHub Settings → Actions\n1461:    - 确保 Actions 已启用\n1462:    - 配置权限设置\n1463: \n1464: 4. **首次运行**\n1465:    - 创建测试 PR 验证 CI\n1466:    - 创建测试 tag 验证 CD\n1467:    - 检查所有工作流运行状态\n1468: \n1469: ### 破坏性变更\n1470: 无 - 首次实现。\n1471: \n1472: ### 行为变更\n1473: - PR 必须通过 CI 检查才能合并\n1474: - Tag 推送自动触发发布\n1475: - 依赖自动更新\n1476: \n1477: ## Open Questions\n1478: \n1479: 1. 是否需要集成 Slack/Discord 通知？\n1480: 2. 是否需要支持多环境部署（dev/staging/prod）？\n1481: 3. 是否需要配置自托管 Runner 以降低成本？\n1482: 4. 是否需要集成 SonarQube 代码质量分析？\n1483: 5. 是否需要配置性能基准测试？\n1484: \n1485: ## References\n1486: \n1487: - `project.md` - AgentCube 项目上下文\n1488: - `changes/AR-032/proposal.md` - Dockerfile 多阶段构建\n1489: - `changes/AR-033/proposal.md` - Makefile 构建目标\n1490: - GitHub Actions Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/actions\n1491: - GitHub Actions Marketplace: https://github.com/marketplace?type=actions\n1492: - Trivy Documentation: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/\n1493: - CodeQL Documentation: https://codeql.github.com/\n1494: - Dependabot Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/code-security/dependabot\n\n(End of file - total 1494 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n\n## Purpose\n\n本提案实现 AgentCube 项目的 GitHub Actions CI/CD 流水线体系，为代码质量、构建验证、镜像发布、安全扫描提供自动化流水线。该 CI/CD 体系是 AgentCube 工程化实践的核心基础设施，支撑持续集成、持续交付、质量门禁全流程。\n\n目标是：\n\n1. **代码质量门禁** - 在 PR 和 push 事件中自动运行 lint、typecheck、test，确保代码质量\n2. **构建验证** - 验证 Go 和 Python 代码可编译，Docker 镜像可构建\n3. **多架构支持** - 构建 amd64、arm64 多架构 Docker 镜像，支持异构集群\n4. **镜像发布** - 自动推送镜像到 GHCR，支持版本标签管理（latest, commit-sha, semver）\n5. **安全扫描** - 集成 Trivy 扫描镜像漏洞，集成 CodeQL 扫描代码安全问题\n6. **文档站点** - 自动构建和部署 Docusaurus 文档到 GitHub Pages\n7. **发布自动化** - 创建 GitHub Release，生成变更日志，上传构建产物\n8. **依赖更新** - 自动检测依赖更新，创建 Dependabot PR\n\n本提案基于 AR-032（Dockerfile 多阶段构建）、AR-033（Makefile 构建目标）实现，遵循 GitHub Actions 最佳实践和 AgentCube 工程规范。\n\n## Scope","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775884293663,"end":1775884293678}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884293685,"sessionID":"ses_2850c860affeZNdDKKGycv8yCT","part":{"id":"prt_d7af3d0af001txGAa47NBGBl7e","messageID":"msg_d7af3c2a40015J8ttPjrshjaSu","sessionID":"ses_2850c860affeZNdDKKGycv8yCT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f067c815d63849d4950ed34d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/AR-034-github-actions/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/AR-034-github-actions/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** .github  \n4: **Language:** YAML  \n5: **Size:** L  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Repository Structure & Shared Configuration\n11: \n12: - [ ] **T1.1** Create `.github/workflows/` directory structure\n13:   - Directory: `.github/workflows/`\n14:   - Verify: Directory exists for workflow files\n15: \n16: - [ ] **T1.2** Define reusable path filter configurations\n17:   - Create path filter definitions for: `lint`, `coverage`, `python`, `codegen`, `copyright`\n18:   - Use `dorny/paths-filter` action patterns\n19:   - Verify: All path filters documented in workflow comments\n20: \n21: - [ ] **T1.3** Set up environment variable conventions\n22:   - Document standard env vars: `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY`, `TAG`, `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA`\n23:   - Verify: Consistent naming across all workflows\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## Phase 2: Agentcube CI Workflow (main.yml)\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T2.1** Create `main.yml` workflow file\n30:   - File: `.github/workflows/main.yml`\n31:   - Name: `Agentcube CI Workflow`\n32:   - Verify: Workflow file created with correct name\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T2.2** Define pull_request triggers for main.yml\n35:   - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n36:   - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n37: \n38: - [ ] **T2.3** Create `build` job in main.yml\n39:   - Job ID: `build`\n40:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n41:   - Verify: Job defined with correct runner\n42: \n43: - [ ] **T2.4** Add checkout and Docker setup steps\n44:   - Step: `actions/checkout@v4`\n45:   - Step: `docker/setup-buildx-action@v3`\n46:   - Verify: Repository checkout and Buildx setup complete\n47: \n48: - [ ] **T2.5** Add Docker version verification step\n49:   - Run: `docker --version` and `docker buildx version`\n50:   - Verify: Docker and buildx versions logged\n51: \n52: - [ ] **T2.6** Add make docker-build execution step\n53:   - Run: `make docker-build`\n54:   - Verify: Workload Manager image builds successfully\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## Phase 3: E2E Tests Workflow (e2e.yml)\n59: \n60: - [ ] **T3.1** Create `e2e.yml` workflow file\n61:   - File: `.github/workflows/e2e.yml`\n62:   - Name: `Agentcube E2E Tests`\n63:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n64: \n65: - [ ] **T3.2** Define pull_request triggers for e2e.yml\n66:   - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n67:   - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n68: \n69: - [ ] **T3.3** Create `e2e-test` job in e2e.yml\n70:   - Job ID: `e2e-test`\n71:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n72:   - Verify: Job defined\n73: \n74: - [ ] **T3.4** Add Go 1.23 setup step\n75:   - Use: `actions/setup-go@v5` with `go-version: '1.23'`\n76:   - Verify: Go 1.23 installed\n77: \n78: - [ ] **T3.5** Add Kind cluster installation step\n79:   - Use: `helm/kind-action@v1` with `install_only: true`, `version: v0.30.0`, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`\n80:   - Verify: Kind v0.30.0 installed without cluster creation\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T3.6** Set ARTIFACTS_PATH environment variable\n83:   - Env: `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n84:   - Verify: Environment variable set for log collection\n85: \n86: - [ ] **T3.7** Add make e2e execution step\n87:   - Run: `make e2e`\n88:   - Verify: E2E tests execute via run_e2e.sh\n89: \n90: - [ ] **T3.8** Add failure log upload step\n91:   - Use: `actions/upload-artifact@v4` with `e2e-logs/` on failure\n92:   - Condition: `if: failure()`\n93:   - Verify: Logs uploaded on test failure\n94: \n95: - [ ] **T3.9** Add cleanup step with always condition\n96:   - Run: `make e2e-clean`\n97:   - Condition: `if: always()`\n98:   - Verify: Kind cluster cleaned up after tests\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Phase 4: Lint Workflow (lint.yml)\n103: \n104: - [ ] **T4.1** Create `lint.yml` workflow file\n105:   - File: `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n106:   - Name: `Lint`\n107:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n108: \n109: - [ ] **T4.2** Define pull_request triggers for lint.yml\n110:   - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n111:   - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n112: \n113: - [ ] **T4.3** Create `golangci` job in lint.yml\n114:   - Job ID: `golangci`\n115:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n116:   - Verify: Job defined\n117: \n118: - [ ] **T4.4** Add paths-filter for Go code changes\n119:   - Filter ID: `lint`\n120:   - Paths: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n121:   - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n122:   - Verify: Path filter detects Go-related changes\n123: \n124: - [ ] **T4.5** Add conditional Go 1.24 setup\n125:   - Use: `actions/setup-go@v5` with `go-version: '1.24'`\n126:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.lint == 'true'`\n127:   - Verify: Go setup only when Go code changes\n128: \n129: - [ ] **T4.6** Add make lint execution step\n130:   - Run: `make lint`\n131:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.lint == 'true'`\n132:   - Verify: golangci-lint runs on changed code\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## Phase 5: Python SDK Tests Workflow (python-sdk-tests.yml)\n137: \n138: - [ ] **T5.1** Create `python-sdk-tests.yml` workflow file\n139:   - File: `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml`\n140:   - Name: `Python SDK Tests`\n141:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n142: \n143: - [ ] **T5.2** Define triggers for python-sdk-tests.yml\n144:   - Trigger: `pull_request`, `merge_group`\n145:   - Verify: Both trigger types configured\n146: \n147: - [ ] **T5.3** Create `python-sdk-tests` job\n148:   - Job ID: `python-sdk-tests`\n149:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n150:   - Working directory: `sdk-python`\n151:   - Verify: Job defined with correct working directory\n152: \n153: - [ ] **T5.4** Add paths-filter for SDK changes\n154:   - Filter ID: `sdk`\n155:   - Paths: `sdk-python/**`\n156:   - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n157:   - Verify: Path filter detects SDK changes\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T5.5** Add Python 3.12 setup step\n160:   - Use: `actions/setup-python@v5` with `python-version: '3.12'`\n161:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'`\n162:   - Verify: Python 3.12 installed in sdk-python directory\n163: \n164: - [ ] **T5.6** Add pytest installation step\n165:   - Run: `pip install pytest`\n166:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'`\n167:   - Verify: pytest installed\n168: \n169: - [ ] **T5.7** Add editable package installation step\n170:   - Run: `pip install -e .`\n171:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'`\n172:   - Verify: SDK installed in editable mode\n173: \n174: - [ ] **T5.8** Add pytest execution step\n175:   - Run: `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n176:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'`\n177:   - Verify: All SDK tests execute\n178: \n179: ---\n180: \n181: ## Phase 6: Python Lint Workflow (python-lint.yml)\n182: \n183: - [ ] **T6.1** Create `python-lint.yml` workflow file\n184:   - File: `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`\n185:   - Name: `Python Lint`\n186:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n187: \n188: - [ ] **T6.2** Define pull_request triggers for python-lint.yml\n189:   - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n190:   - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n191: \n192: - [ ] **T6.3** Create `python_lint` job in python-lint.yml\n193:   - Job ID: `python_lint`\n194:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n195:   - Verify: Job defined\n196: \n197: - [ ] **T6.4** Add paths-filter for Python code changes\n198:   - Filter ID: `python`\n199:   - Paths: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`\n200:   - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n201:   - Verify: Path filter detects Python-related changes\n202: \n203: - [ ] **T6.5** Add Python 3.10 setup step\n204:   - Use: `actions/setup-python@v5` with `python-version: '3.10'`\n205:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'`\n206:   - Verify: Python 3.10 installed\n207: \n208: - [ ] **T6.6** Add Ruff installation step\n209:   - Run: `pip install ruff`\n210:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'`\n211:   - Verify: Ruff installed\n212: \n213: - [ ] **T6.7** Add Ruff check execution step\n214:   - Run: `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n215:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'`\n216:   - Working directory: repository root\n217:   - Verify: Ruff linting runs from repo root\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Phase 7: Test Coverage Workflow (test-coverage.yml)\n222: \n223: - [ ] **T7.1** Create `test-coverage.yml` workflow file\n224:   - File: `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml`\n225:   - Name: `Test Coverage`\n226:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T7.2** Define triggers for test-coverage.yml\n229:   - Trigger: `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call`\n230:   - Verify: All three trigger types configured\n231: \n232: - [ ] **T7.3** Add workflow_call inputs for CODECOV_TOKEN\n233:   - Input: `CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional, string)\n234:   - Verify: Token can be passed from reusable workflows\n235: \n236: - [ ] **T7.4** Create `coverage` job in test-coverage.yml\n237:   - Job ID: `coverage`\n238:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n239:   - Verify: Job defined\n240: \n241: - [ ] **T7.5** Add paths-filter for coverage\n242:   - Filter ID: `coverage`\n243:   - Paths: `**` excluding `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`\n244:   - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n245:   - Verify: Path filter excludes non-code files\n246: \n247: - [ ] **T7.6** Add free disk space step\n248:   - Run: Disk cleanup commands for runner\n249:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'`\n250:   - Verify: More disk space available for Go modules\n251: \n252: - [ ] **T7.7** Add Go 1.24 setup step\n253:   - Use: `actions/setup-go@v5` with `go-version: '1.24'`\n254:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'`\n255:   - Verify: Go 1.24 installed\n256: \n257: - [ ] **T7.8** Add go test with coverage step\n258:   - Run: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n259:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'`\n260:   - Verify: Coverage report generated\n261: \n262: - [ ] **T7.9** Add coverage summary to GitHub step summary\n263:   - Run: Generate coverage percentage and write to `$GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY`\n264:   - Verify: Coverage displayed in workflow UI\n265: \n266: - [ ] **T7.10** Add Codecov upload step\n267:   - Use: `codecov/codecov-action@v4`\n268:   - With: `token: ${{ secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN }}`, `files: coverage.out`\n269:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true' && secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN != ''`\n270:   - Verify: Coverage uploaded to Codecov when token available\n271: \n272: - [ ] **T7.11** Add coverage artifact upload step\n273:   - Use: `actions/upload-artifact@v4` with name `go-coverage`, path `coverage.out`\n274:   - Verify: Coverage file available as artifact\n275: \n276: ---\n277: \n278: ## Phase 8: Codegen Check Workflow (codegen-check.yml)\n279: \n280: - [ ] **T8.1** Create `codegen-check.yml` workflow file\n281:   - File: `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml`\n282:   - Name: `Codegen Check`\n283:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n284: \n285: - [ ] **T8.2** Define pull_request triggers for codegen-check.yml\n286:   - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n287:   - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n288: \n289: - [ ] **T8.3** Create `codegen-check` job in codegen-check.yml\n290:   - Job ID: `codegen-check`\n291:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n292:   - Verify: Job defined\n293: \n294: - [ ] **T8.4** Add paths-filter for codegen changes\n295:   - Filter ID: `codegen`\n296:   - Paths: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile`\n297:   - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n298:   - Verify: Path filter detects API/codegen changes\n299: \n300: - [ ] **T8.5** Add Go 1.24.4 setup step\n301:   - Use: `actions/setup-go@v5` with `go-version: '1.24.4'`\n302:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.codegen == 'true'`\n303:   - Verify: Go 1.24.4 installed\n304: \n305: - [ ] **T8.6** Add make gen-check execution step\n306:   - Run: `make gen-check`\n307:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.codegen == 'true'`\n308:   - Verify: Generated code matches committed code\n309: \n310: ---\n311: \n312: ## Phase 9: Copyright Check Workflow (copyright-check.yml)\n313: \n314: - [ ] **T9.1** Create `copyright-check.yml` workflow file\n315:   - File: `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml`\n316:   - Name: `Copyright Check`\n317:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n318: \n319: - [ ] **T9.2** Define pull_request triggers for copyright-check.yml\n320:   - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n321:   - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n322: \n323: - [ ] **T9.3** Create `build` job in copyright-check.yml\n324:   - Job ID: `build`\n325:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n326:   - Verify: Job defined\n327: \n328: - [ ] **T9.4** Add paths-filter for copyright changes\n329:   - Filter ID: `copyright`\n330:   - Paths: All files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**`\n331:   - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n332:   - Verify: Path filter detects source code changes\n333: \n334: - [ ] **T9.5** Add moreutils installation step\n335:   - Run: `sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y moreutils`\n336:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.copyright == 'true'`\n337:   - Verify: `sponge` command available\n338: \n339: - [ ] **T9.6** Add make gen-copyright execution step\n340:   - Run: `make gen-copyright`\n341:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.copyright == 'true'`\n342:   - Verify: Copyright headers generated\n343: \n344: - [ ] **T9.7** Add git diff check step\n345:   - Run: `git diff --exit-code`\n346:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.copyright == 'true'`\n347:   - Verify: No uncommitted copyright changes\n348: \n349: ---\n350: \n351: ## Phase 10: Codespell Workflow (codespell.yml)\n352: \n353: - [ ] **T10.1** Create `codespell.yml` workflow file\n354:   - File: `.github/workflows/codespell.yml`\n355:   - Name: `Codespell`\n356:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n357: \n358: - [ ] **T10.2** Define pull_request triggers for codespell.yml\n359:   - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n360:   - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n361: \n362: - [ ] **T10.3** Create `codespell` job in codespell.yml\n363:   - Job ID: `codespell`\n364:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n365:   - Verify: Job defined\n366: \n367: - [ ] **T10.4** Add checkout step\n368:   - Use: `actions/checkout@v4`\n369:   - Verify: Repository checked out\n370: \n371: - [ ] **T10.5** Add backup problematic files step\n372:   - Run: Backup `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json` at root and nested\n373:   - Use: `mv` to temporary location\n374:   - Verify: Files backed up before codespell\n375: \n376: - [ ] **T10.6** Add codespell installation step\n377:   - Run: `pip install codespell`\n378:   - Verify: codespell installed\n379: \n380: - [ ] **T10.7** Add codespell execution step\n381:   - Run: `codespell --check-filenames --skip '*.min.js,*.lock' --ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn .`\n382:   - Verify: Spelling check runs with correct skip/ignore lists\n383: \n384: - [ ] **T10.8** Add restore backed-up files step\n385:   - Run: Restore backed-up files to original locations\n386:   - Condition: `if: always()`\n387:   - Verify: Repository restored to original state\n388: \n389: ---\n390: \n391: ## Phase 11: Build and Push Release Images (build-push-release.yml)\n392: \n393: - [ ] **T11.1** Create `build-push-release.yml` workflow file\n394:   - File: `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml`\n395:   - Name: `Build and Push Release Images`\n396:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n397: \n398: - [ ] **T11.2** Define push triggers for build-push-release.yml\n399:   - Trigger: `push` to `main`\n400:   - Trigger: `push` tags `v*.*.*` and `v*.*.*-*`\n401:   - Verify: Both branch and tag triggers configured\n402: \n403: - [ ] **T11.3** Create `build-and-push` job\n404:   - Job ID: `build-and-push`\n405:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n406:   - Verify: Job defined\n407: \n408: - [ ] **T11.4** Add checkout step (v3)\n409:   - Use: `actions/checkout@v3`\n410:   - Verify: Repository checked out\n411: \n412: - [ ] **T11.5** Add Go 1.24.4 setup step (v4)\n413:   - Use: `actions/setup-go@v4` with `go-version: '1.24.4'`\n414:   - Verify: Go 1.24.4 installed\n415: \n416: - [ ] **T11.6** Add Docker Buildx setup step (v2)\n417:   - Use: `docker/setup-buildx-action@v2`\n418:   - Verify: Buildx configured\n419: \n420: - [ ] **T11.7** Add Docker login to GHCR step\n421:   - Use: `docker/login-action@v3` with `registry: ghcr.io`, `username: ${{ github.actor }}`, `password: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}`\n422:   - Verify: Authenticated to ghcr.io\n423: \n424: - [ ] **T11.8** Add TAG environment variable logic\n425:   - If `github.ref_type == 'tag'`: `TAG = github.ref_name`\n426:   - Else: `TAG = latest`\n427:   - Run: Shell logic to set TAG\n428:   - Verify: Correct tag selected based on ref type\n429: \n430: - [ ] **T11.9** Add workload manager buildx push step\n431:   - Run: `make docker-buildx-push` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`\n432:   - Verify: Multi-arch image built and pushed\n433: \n434: - [ ] **T11.10** Add router buildx push step\n435:   - Run: `make docker-buildx-push-router` with same IMAGE_REGISTRY\n436:   - Verify: Router image built and pushed\n437: \n438: - [ ] **T11.11** Add picod buildx push step\n439:   - Run: `make docker-buildx-push-picod` with same IMAGE_REGISTRY\n440:   - Verify: Picod image built and pushed\n441: \n442: ---\n443: \n444: ## Phase 12: Dify Plugin Publish (dify-plugin-publish.yml)\n445: \n446: - [ ] **T12.1** Create `dify-plugin-publish.yml` workflow file\n447:   - File: `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml`\n448:   - Name: `Dify Plugin Publish`\n449:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n450: \n451: - [ ] **T12.2** Define push tag triggers for dify-plugin-publish.yml\n452:   - Trigger: `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*`\n453:   - Verify: Tag pattern configured\n454: \n455: - [ ] **T12.3** Create `publish` job in dify-plugin-publish.yml\n456:   - Job ID: `publish`\n457:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n458:   - Verify: Job defined\n459: \n460: - [ ] **T12.4** Add dify-plugin CLI download step\n461:   - Run: Download `dify-plugin` CLI v0.0.6 from GitHub releases\n462:   - Verify: CLI binary installed\n463: \n464: - [ ] **T12.5** Add yq installation step\n465:   - Run: Install `yq` for YAML processing\n466:   - Verify: yq available\n467: \n468: - [ ] **T12.6** Add manifest.yaml parsing step\n469:   - Run: Extract plugin metadata using yq\n470:   - Verify: Plugin name/version extracted\n471: \n472: - [ ] **T12.7** Add plugin packaging step\n473:   - Run: `dify-plugin package` to create plugin bundle\n474:   - Verify: Plugin packaged successfully\n475: \n476: - [ ] **T12.8** Add author repository checkout step\n477:   - Use: `actions/checkout@v4` with `repository: author/dify-plugins`, `token: ${{ secrets.PLUGIN_ACTION }}`\n478:   - Verify: Author repository checked out\n479: \n480: - [ ] **T12.9** Add plugin file move step\n481:   - Run: Move `.difypkg` file to correct location\n482:   - Verify: Plugin file in place\n483: \n484: - [ ] **T12.10** Add git branch, commit, push step\n485:   - Run: Create branch, commit changes, push to author repo\n486:   - Verify: Changes committed and pushed\n487: \n488: - [ ] **T12.11** Add PR creation step\n489:   - Run: `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` with `GH_TOKEN`\n490:   - Use: `github/gh-cli` or similar\n491:   - Verify: Pull request created for plugin submission\n492: \n493: ---\n494: \n495: ## Phase 13: Workflow Approval (workflows-approve.yml)\n496: \n497: - [ ] **T13.1** Create `workflows-approve.yml` workflow file\n498:   - File: `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml`\n499:   - Name: `Approve Workflows`\n500:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n501: \n502: - [ ] **T13.2** Define pull_request_target triggers\n503:   - Trigger: `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` to `main`, `release-**`\n504:   - Verify: Correct event types and branches configured\n505: \n506: - [ ] **T13.3** Create `approve` job in workflows-approve.yml\n507:   - Job ID: `approve`\n508:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n509:   - Verify: Job defined\n510: \n511: - [ ] **T13.4** Add GitHub script step for contributor check\n512:   - Use: `actions/github-script@v7`\n513:   - Script: List contributor PRs to determine if first-time\n514:   - Verify: First-time contributor status determined\n515: \n516: - [ ] **T13.5** Add ok-to-test label check logic\n517:   - Script: Check if PR has `ok-to-test` label\n518:   - Verify: Label presence detected\n519: \n520: - [ ] **T13.6** Add conditional workflow run approval\n521:   - Condition: If NOT first-time OR has `ok-to-test` label\n522:   - Script: List workflow runs for head SHA with `status: action_required`\n523:   - Use: `github.rest.actions.approveWorkflowRun()` for each\n524:   - Verify: Pending workflow runs approved\n525: \n526: ---\n527: \n528: ## Phase 14: Workflow Testing & Validation\n529: \n530: - [ ] **T14.1** Test main.yml workflow locally with act\n531:   - Command: `act pull_request -j build` (if act available)\n532:   - Verify: Workflow syntax valid\n533: \n534: - [ ] **T14.2** Validate all workflow YAML syntax\n535:   - Run: `yamllint .github/workflows/*.yml` or similar\n536:   - Verify: All workflows pass YAML linting\n537: \n538: - [ ] **T14.3** Test path filters with sample PR\n539:   - Create test PR with Go file changes\n540:   - Verify: lint.yml triggers correctly\n541: \n542: - [ ] **T14.4** Test path filters with Python changes\n543:   - Create test PR with sdk-python changes\n544:   - Verify: python-sdk-tests.yml and python-lint.yml trigger\n545: \n546: - [ ] **T14.5** Test codespell workflow\n547:   - Introduce intentional typo in source file\n548:   - Verify: codespell.yml fails on PR\n549: \n550: - [ ] **T14.6** Test build-push-release.yml with test tag\n551:   - Push test tag `v9.9.9-test`\n552:   - Verify: Images built and pushed to GHCR\n553: \n554: - [ ] **T14.7** Verify Codecov integration\n555:   - Run test-coverage.yml on PR\n556:   - Verify: Coverage report uploads (if token configured)\n557: \n558: - [ ] **T14.8** Test e2e.yml workflow\n559:   - Create PR to main\n560:   - Verify: E2E tests run in Kind cluster\n561:   - Verify: Logs uploaded on failure\n562: \n563: ---\n564: \n565: ## Acceptance Criteria\n566: \n567: 1. ✅ All 12 workflow files created in `.github/workflows/`\n568: 2. ✅ `main.yml` builds Workload Manager Docker image on PR\n569: 3. ✅ `e2e.yml` runs E2E tests with Kind v0.30.0, captures logs\n570: 4. ✅ `lint.yml` runs golangci-lint only when Go code changes\n571: 5. ✅ `python-sdk-tests.yml` runs pytest on SDK changes\n572: 6. ✅ `python-lint.yml` runs Ruff from repo root on Python changes\n573: 7. ✅ `test-coverage.yml` runs coverage tests, uploads to Codecov\n574: 8. ✅ `codegen-check.yml` verifies generated code is up to date\n575: 9. ✅ `copyright-check.yml` ensures copyright headers are consistent\n576: 10. ✅ `codespell.yml` checks spelling with proper skip/ignore lists\n577: 11. ✅ `build-push-release.yml` publishes multi-arch images on tags\n578: 12. ✅ `dify-plugin-publish.yml` packages and submits Dify plugin\n579: 13. ✅ `workflows-approve.yml` auto-approves workflows for repeat contributors\n580: 14. ✅ All workflows use correct path filters via dorny/paths-filter\n581: 15. ✅ All workflows have proper conditional execution based on path changes\n582: 16. ✅ Release workflow uses correct action versions (v3/v4/v2 for compatibility)\n583: 17. ✅ E2E workflow captures and uploads failure artifacts\n584: 18. ✅ Coverage workflow supports workflow_call with optional token\n585: 19. ✅ All workflow names match specification\n586: 20. ✅ All triggers target correct branches (main, release-*)\n587: \n588: ---\n589: \n590: **Notes:**\n591: - Stage ST-3: Implementation complete (all 12 GitHub Actions workflows created)\n592: - Workflows cover: CI build, E2E, lint (Go/Python), SDK tests, coverage, codegen, copyright, codespell, release publishing, Dify plugin, workflow approval\n593: - Path filtering via `dorny/paths-filter@v3` for efficient conditional execution\n594: - E2E uses Kind with `install_only: true` to avoid double cluster creation\n595: - Release workflow publishes multi-arch images to GHCR\n596: - First-time contributor workflow approval prevents abuse while enabling CI\n597: \n598: (End of file)\n\n(End of file - total 598 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) Tasks\n\n**Module:** .github  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Repository Structure & Shared Configuration\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create `.github/workflows/` directory structure\n  - Directory: `.github/workflows/`\n  - Verify: Directory exists for workflow files\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Define reusable path filter configurations\n  - Create path filter definitions for: `lint`, `coverage`, `python`, `codegen`, `copyright`\n  - Use `dorny/paths-filter` action patterns\n  - Verify: All path filters documented in workflow comments\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/AR-034-github-actions/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775884293666,"end":1775884293682}}}}
